article.headline: Youngstown State 51, Slippery Rock 21
article.story: YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio (AP) -- Marcus Mason rushed for 101 yards and three touchdowns Thursday night to lead Youngstown State past Slippery Rock 51-21. Mason had a 48-yard touchdown run in the third quarter after scoring runs of 1 and 6 yards in the first half. Youngstown State (1-0) racked up 424 yards of offense, holding Slippery Rock (0-1) to 282. Tom Zetts hit Rory Berry with a 20-yard pass in the second and Da'Michael Horne with a 21-yard pass in the third for the Penguins. Zetts was 10-of-13 for 118 yards. Nate Crookshank went 15-of-22 for 194 yards, with short TD passes to Colin Golden and Luke Wetzel. Monquantae Gibson started the second quarter with a 54-yard run to the Slippery Rock 3. He took it in on the next snap. Travis Sarver had a 29-yard scoring run in the third quarter for Slippery Rock. Youngstown State had the last two scores of the game, a safety and a 33-yard pass from backup quarterback Mike Schneider to Brandon Nicholson.
